<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870218-0050 </DOCNO><HL> Triton Energy Corp. Sells2.7 Million New Shares</HL><DD> 02/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> OILSTOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><DATELINE> DALLAS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Triton Energy Corp. said it sold 2.7 million newly issued shares in the U.S. and Canada at $17 each.    In addition, 300,000 existing shares were sold in the U.S. by a holder, Triton said.    Triton closed at $15.75, up 75 cents, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday.    Triton's proceeds will be used to pay bank debt, the oil and gas exploration and production concern said. With Triton's sale, 14.6 million shares are outstanding.    The 300,000 existing shares were sold by National Coal Board Staff Superannuation Scheme Trustees Ltd., a United Kingdom pension fund, which still owns 576,000 shares.    The U.S. offering of two million shares, including the holder's shares, was underwritten by Shearson Lehman Brothers Inc. The Canadian offering of one million shares was underwritten by Wood Gundy Inc. </TEXT></DOC>